quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  22,6,"This is because God is the Reality. It is He Who gives life to the dead, and it is He Who has power over all things"
  22,7,"And indeed the Hour will come. There can be no doubt about it, or about the fact that God will raise up all who are in the graves"
  22,8,"Yet there are among humanity, those who dispute about God, without knowledge, without guidance, and without a book of enlightenment"
  22,9,"Bending his side, in order to lead the people astray from the path of God, for him there is disgrace in this life, and on the Day of Accountability, We will make him taste the penalty of burning"
  22,10,â€œThis is because of the deeds which your hands sent forth. For indeed God is not unjust to His servants
  22,11,"There are among the people some who serve God on the verge. If good befalls them, they are content, but if a trial comes to them, they turn on their faces. They lose both the present and the hereafter. That is a loss for all to see"
  22,12,"They call on such deities besides God, who can neither hurt nor profit them. That is straying far indeed"
  22,13,"They call on one whose harm is nearer than his profit. Harmful indeed is the protector, and harmful the companion"
  22,14,"Indeed God will admit those who believe and work righteous deeds to gardens beneath which rivers flow, for God carries out all that He plans"
  22,15,"If any think that God will not help His messenger in the present and the hereafter, let him stretch out a rope to the ceiling and cut himself off, then let him see whether his plan will remove that which enrages him"